response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Check if a list contains all unique elements\", \"description\": \"Write a function that checks if all elements in a given list are unique. If any element appears more than once, return `False`. Otherwise, return `True`.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```\\ndef has_unique_elements(lst: list) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `lst` (list): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if all elements in the input list are unique, `False` otherwise.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\nimport collections\\n\\ndef has_unique_elements(lst: list) -> bool:\\n    return len(lst) == len(collections.Counter(lst))\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert has_unique_elements([1, 2, 3]) == True\", \"assert has_unique_elements([1, 1, 2]) == False\", \"assert has_unique_elements([]) == True\"] }"
